Uses of Package
org.shared.parallel

  • Packages that use org.shared.parallel 
    Package Description
    org.shared.parallel
    A framework for specifying and executing parallel dataflow engines.
  • Classes in org.shared.parallel used by org.shared.parallel 
    Class and Description
    Calculator
    Defines an atomic calculation as part of a parallel dataflow graph.
    Edge
    Defines an edge relationship between two nodes.
    Engine.EngineEdge
    An output-input relationship between two Engine.EngineNodes.
    Engine.EngineNode
    A computation node that is part of some topology of nodes.
    Handle
    Defines a container for storing the results of Calculators.
    LimitedMemoryPolicy.PolicyNode
    An Engine.EngineNode proxy class that aids in the computation of traversal orderings.
    Traversable
    Defines a graph node as part of some total ordering on graph nodes.
    TraversalPolicy
    Defines a total ordering and depth assignment to a collection of Traversables via Traversable.setOrder(int) and Traversable.setDepth(int).
